modules.description: Provides hash functions including SHA-256, SHA-512, and BLAKE2b, along with HMAC variants, and cryptographic operations for Ed25519 such as key generation, signing, and verification. Works with byte sequences, private and public keys, and cryptographic contexts. Used for secure message authentication, digital signatures, and key management in protocol implementations.

Provides cryptographic operations including key generation, signing, verification, and hashing with SHA-256, SHA-512, and BLAKE2b. Works with private and public key types, expanded keys, and raw string data. Used for generating digital signatures, encrypting messages with secret keys, and authenticating data with HMAC.
